Rating: 4
I LOVE this recipe! This IS the recipe given to me by my German grandmother (who got it from her grandmother), except it never had rosemary or mustard in it and had a lot more onion. I use about 2 medium onions for 3-4 lbs of potatoes. I cook the onions in the bacon fat until translucent before sprinking with the flour and cooking a bit more. Lately I have modified it slightly from my grandmother's original by using small boiled red potatoes leaving the skins on and then quartering them. (She always peeled them.) It's good to make this a day ahead to let the sweet and sour sauce soak in well and then reheat before serving. (A couple of times I have had so- called German potato salad served cold. Blech!) The essence of this recipe is the sweet and sour sauce. I usually use cider vinegar and cook it to the consistancy of thin gravy before pouring over the cut potatoes.

