Rating: 4
I made this for Mother's Day and it was a hit! I made a lot of changes based on other people's reviews. Here's a summary of the changes: Double the amount of bacon and cut it up before frying to save time. But, cut back on the amount of bacon grease. Bake potatoes (yukon gold) to almost done instead of boiling them, then cut them up. (About 4 lbs). Use (just under) 1/4 c sugar, 1/2 c vinegar, 1/4 t rosemary, one half cup onion, 1 t salt, 2 t prepared german mustard (instead of powdered mustard). Brown flour and onion in bacon grease before adding the rest of the ingredients. Make this the day before and reheat in 350 oven for 45 min. Delish!

